.SH NAME
craig \- Discord bot with disappointed dad personality
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B craig-start
.br
.B craig-stop
.br
.B craig-restart
.br
.B craig-status
.br
.B craig-log
.SH DESCRIPTION
Craig is a Discord bot that responds like a disappointed, divorced father. He reacts to trigger phrases and direct mentions with a large pool of humorous, disapproving responses.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B craig-start
Start the Craig bot service.
.TP
.B craig-stop
Stop the Craig bot service.
.TP
.B craig-restart
Restart the Craig bot service. Use this after editing .env to apply changes.
.TP
.B craig-status
Display the current status of the Craig bot service.
.TP
.B craig-log
Follow the Craig bot logs in real time using journalctl. Press Ctrl+C to exit.
.SH INSTALLATION
To install Craig from the project directory:

    chmod +x Scripts/install.sh
    sudo Scripts/install.sh

The installer will:
.IP \(bu 2
Create an isolated Python virtual environment
.IP \(bu 2
Install dependencies (discord.py, python-dotenv)
.IP \(bu 2
Prompt for your Discord bot token (or reuse existing token)
.IP \(bu 2
Configure systemd service for auto-start on boot
.IP \(bu 2
Install management command aliases to /usr/local/bin/

.SH UNINSTALL
To uninstall Craig:

    sudo Scripts/uninstall.sh

The script will stop the service, remove systemd configuration, and optionally delete bot files.

.SH CONFIGURATION
Craig's behavior is configured in the .env file in the project root. Edit with:

    $EDITOR .env

Variables:
.TP
.B DISCORD_TOKEN
Your Discord bot token (required)
.TP
.B RESPONSE_CHANCE
Probability (0.0-1.0) that Craig reacts to trigger phrases (default: 0.5)
.TP
.B LOG_FILE
Path to the log file for debugging (default: craig.log)
.TP
.B COMMAND_PREFIX
Reserved for future commands (default: !)

After editing .env, run:

    craig-restart

.SH SLASH COMMANDS
In Discord, use these slash commands:

/dadjoke - Get a random disappointed dad response
.br
/roast [target] - Get roasted by Craig
.br
/wisdom - Craig shares a life lesson
.br
/sigh - Craig sighs in disappointment

.SH TRIGGER PHRASES
Craig automatically responds to 50+ trigger phrases including:

- Insults: "fuck you", "screw you", "fuck off"
- Disbelief: "are you kidding me", "yeah right", "no way"
- Exasperation: "what the hell", "this is bullshit"
- Frustration: "fuck this", "how stupid"

He also always responds when his name is mentioned anywhere in a message.

.SH LOGS
View recent logs:

    craig-log

View logs from the current boot:

    journalctl -u craig-bot -b

View logs from the past hour:

    journalctl -u craig-bot --since "1 hour ago"

